This paper deals with improving the accuracy of crowd counting using deep neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new network architecture, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the safety and management implications of crowd counting, which could fall under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
